<H2 ALIGN="center">Open your account</H2>

<P>Once you have managed to connect to freeserve using their setup login
&amp; password details, you need to connect to a special webpage using a
Browser that can handle SSL and cookies (The latest versions of Ibrowse,
Voyager &amp; AwebII should all work...). You will have to connect to the
following page (you will not be able to access this unless you're
connected to Freeserve).</P>

<P>It's a good idea to choose a password and two usernames (in case your
first choice is already in use) beforehand to save time online.</P>

<P><B>https://signup.freeserve.net</B></P>


<P>Follow the online prompts, filling (annoyingly, all details, some of
them I'd rather not answer...). When you click on finish, you will be
prompted to download a file, although it is small, it is for PC users &amp;
is of no use to you (unless you have a PC of course ;)). If you get an
error (like I did) when you click to finally set up your account, press
you browser's Back button &amp; try again - chances are that the server is
too busy at the time to process your request. Make a note of the details
on the last page and log off.</P>


<P>You will then need to change the Login &amp; Password to the ones you
chose in your tcp/ip stack or dialer.</P>


<P><FONT COLOR="red">Please note:</FONT> You will have to enter
everything after the "@" in your e-mail address in the login field of
your TCP stack, other wise you will not be able to log in!</P>

